# 1\. Introduction

This document presents the requirement analysis for the Online Banking Application. It outlines the key actors, use cases, functional and non-functional requirements, and areas requiring clarification. The purpose is to ensure a shared understanding between business stakeholders and the technical team before proceeding to architecture and implementation. The case-study document is attached in Appendix section.

# 2\. Actors

• Customer (End User): Registers, logs in, performs banking operations.

• Bank Staff (Approver/Admin): Approves registrations, manages cheque clearance, configures limits.

• System (iNB Application): Provides UI, processes transactions, enforces rules.

# 3\. Use Cases

## UC1: Customer Registration

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer has access to the iNB portal.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Customer fills registration form (account type, personal details).
*   \- Request sent to bank staff for approval.
*   \- Bank staff approves → account created.
*   \- Customer notified (letter/email/SMS).
*   \- Customer can log in after approval.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Should approval be manual only or automated workflow?
*   \- Notification method (postal letter, email, SMS)?
*   \- Any KYC/document upload required?

## UC2: Login & Home Page

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer account approved.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Customer enters username/password.
*   \- System validates credentials.
*   \- Home page displays account balance and summary.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Should home page show only balance or also recent transactions, alerts, offers?
*   \- Should login support multi-factor authentication?
*   \- Mobile/responsive design required?

## UC3: Account Management (Savings & Current)

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer has an active account.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Savings Account: Interest applied monthly, withdrawal limits enforced, min balance required.
*   \- Current Account: Zero balance allowed overdraft facility with daily interest charges.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Are withdrawal limits/min balance global or per-customer configurable?
*   \- Should overdraft charges trigger daily notifications?
*   \- Interest rate changes — who manages configuration?

## UC4: Statements

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer is logged in.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Mini statement: last 5 transactions.
*   \- Detailed statement: user-defined date range.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Should statements include pending transactions?
*   \- Export options (PDF, Excel)?

## UC5: Cheque Deposits

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer has a cheque to deposit.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Customer fills online slip, prints, attaches to cheque, sends to bank.
*   \- Bank staff updates status: Not Received → Sent for Clearance → Cleared/Bounced.
*   \- Customer checks status online.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Should customers be notified of status changes via email/SMS?
*   \- Bounced cheque fine — fixed or configurable?
*   \- SLA for cheque clearance (always 3 days or configurable)?

## UC6: Reconciliation Report

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Bank staff is logged in.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Generate report of cheques received, cleared, bounced, pending.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Who consumes reports (staff, auditors, customers)?
*   \- Export formats required (PDF, Excel)?
*   \- Frequency of report generation?

## UC7: Bill Payments

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer is logged in.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Customer pays utility bills immediately or schedules for later.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Should recurring payments be supported?
*   \- Integration with external biller APIs?
*   \- Real-time vs batch processing?

## UC8: Money Transfer

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer is logged in.

• Main Flow:

*   \- Customer transfers money to another iNB account.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Should transfers to external banks be supported?
*   \- Real-time confirmation required?
*   \- Transaction limits configurable?

## UC9: Security

• Actors: Customer, Bank Staff, System

• Preconditions: Customer attempts login.

• Main Flow:

*   \- After 3 failed login attempts, account locked → manual reactivation.

• Clarifications Needed:

*   \- Should system support two-factor authentication?
*   \- Encryption standards for data at rest/in transit?
*   \- Audit logging requirements?

# 5\. Functional Requirements

• Customer registration and approval workflow.

• Login and home page with account summary.

• Savings and Current account management with interest, limits, overdraft.

• Mini and detailed account statements.

• Cheque deposit tracking and status updates.

• Reconciliation reports for cheques.

• Bill payment (immediate and scheduled).

• Money transfer between accounts.

• Security features like login lockout and manual reactivation.

# 6\. Non-Functional Requirements

• Performance: Fast response times under load.

• Scalability: Support for growing number of users and transactions.

• Usability: Intuitive UI with minimal clicks and consistent design.

• Configurability: Admin-configurable limits, interest rates, charges.

• Reliability: Accurate processing of transactions and cheque statuses.

• Deployment: Must run on IIS.

• Security: Data encryption, login lockout, audit logging, optional 2FA.
